description: Meeting point: Outside the shop  Closest HUB - AGORA learning centre (for bread only) or Hal5.   Wait outside the shop for other volunteers.  Do not forget to bring your own bags for the pickup.  If it's too much to carry, please ask for additional help via the Whatsapp group. The entire quantity has to be picked up. Excess must be dropped at the hub.  Post a picture of the hub on FB/ig to inform others of the food (Read the detailed description of the pickup before your first pickup)

Meeting point: just inside the shop (read full info by clicking on the shop's name above!)  ⌚ You _can not_ enter after closing time, so be on time!   Closest HUB: Hub Agora  Do not forget to bring your own bags.  It can be a lot so bring enough bags! the entire quantity has to be picked up. The excess can be dropped at hubs  Post a picture of the hub on FB/ig to inform other members about the food. (Read the detailed description of the pickup before your first pickup).

Post a picture of the hub on FB/ig to inform other members about the food. (Read the detailed description of the pickup before your first pickup).

Beer give-away (second and probably last chance)!   More than 50 boxes of 24 bottles each of craft beer ('luxury pilsner'), best before date of 8/2023 but still very good. More flavorful than a regular Stella/Jupiler/etc! To cover the transportation cost (they had to rent a van), there is a symbolic price of 2 euro per box of 24 bottles. We'll open a few bottles so you can taste it first.  Practical info:  Tuesday 23 April, from 6pm till 7pm Redingenhof 14, 3000 Leuven at the white garage door. Payment cash only in the exact amount if possible. First come, first served; take as many boxes as you want. See you there and tell your friends!  More info on the beer: https://drblues.com/our-beer/pacemaker/

Meeting point: School HDC, Oude Markt, 3000 Leuven; entrance at the side (Parijsstraat), through the brown wooden door.  Be there on time. Wait outside the entrance for others (who have signed up for pickup). When complete, go in.  Let them know that you are from 'FSL' and are here to pick up leftover food.   It's a Flemisch buffet with meet dishes, veggie and mashed potatoes. They will put the leftovers in food buckets (clean and food-safe)  However, be ready with bike bags or grocery bags to carry the food buckets.  The entire quantity has to be picked up. Share the excess food with your friends and family  Post a picture of the hub on whatsapp/FB/ig to share it with other volunteers.  Emergency contact: Ingrid Wevers, +32 497 03 31 43

Beer give-away!   More than 100 boxes of 24 bottles of pilsner each (4.5% alcohol), best before date of 8/2023 but still good. To cover the transportation cost (they had to rent a van), there is a symbolic price of 2 euro per box of 24 bottles. We'll open a few bottles so you can taste it first.  It starts at 11am this Saturday (30th) @ Redingenhof 14, 3000 Leuven at the white garage door. Payment cash only in the exact amount if possible. First come, first served. See you there and tell your friends! (There is no limit on the number of pickup slots and you can take as many boxes as you like. The goal is to have everything gone!)  More info on the beer: https://drblues.com/our-beer/pacemaker/
